<br>
Take for example ToV, the added saves are nice, but even with good resists you're still going to take damage and need healing.  Healers aren't going to want to waste mana on pets, so while the changes mean pets will last longer against AoEs, they will eventually die.  Is it worth resummoning pets over and over?<br>
<br>
What about pathing?  Will Magi really be allowed to use pets in places like Hate now?  I for one doubt it.  Regardless of how things are supposed to work, no one is going to want to risk long CR just to get a little extra damage by allowing pets.<br>
<br>
Call my a glass half empty kinda guy, but I just don't see raid leaders suddenly allowing pets in all the places they have been forbidden.  Even if they were allowed, controlling the pet is going to detract from mod rod duty and the occasional nuking.<br>
<br>
