</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uconjurous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Conjurous</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#333333>(7/28/02 12:18:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are pets really a viable raiding tool?</span><hr size=1> I did ToV the other night with my pet, it was ok, epic pet would usually lose 50% or more hp b4 the mob was dead, but if your guild is chain pulling then pet is unlikely to survive 2 AE mobs in a row, gotta keep him out of AE sight till mob is properly engaged though. Also gotta keep an eye out for when the mob enrages, saw other mages Water pet go down in 2 secsonds when that happened. I am only 59 so it might be better for L60 mages there. <p><center><b><a target="new"href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=66965">Conjurous Magnifico</a></b></center><center>59th Conjurer</center><center><TABLE><TR>
