Kinda fun to see 7 pets die in like .3 sec then Burrower enrages  :-).<br>
Other good tip, pull out pet in GOOD time before Shei enrages  :-).<br>
Kinda fun after fighting a mob as clean as you can do for something like 15 mins on enrage 3 pets die and spawn 3 new mobs  :-). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uusrbinperldashw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>usrbinperl dashw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#333333>(7/28/02 12:42:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are pets really a viable raiding tool?</span><hr size=1> Hmm, see that's pretty much what I thought...  What I'm getting at here is that pets are a flawed way of delivery damage to most encounters that require multiple groups.<br>
<br>
While all the pet changes are most welcome and certainly make XP'ing and finding groups easier, they do little to nothing to balance Magi in the raiding aspect of the game.  Something else needs to be done to give Magi a function other than modrod'ing (for that matter, do something for Necros, too).<br>
<br>
Unfortunately a lot of class abilities and specialties from grouping purposes are useless on raids, or only require one or two of a particular class to fill that function.  This primarily effects casters, as another melee always means more damage, which is a good thing.<br>
<br>
The classes most affected by this, IMHO, are Necromancer, Druid, Magician, and Enchanter.<br>
<br>
Necro: Pretty much their only function on raids is twitch.  If there is an epic'd Necro, he DoTs when it will stick, but only one per fight can do that.  I don't think I have <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> ever</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> seen a Necro use their new &quot;group/raid friendly&quot; group taps on a raid (even if they did, how useful would it be?).  Main grouping functions of pet for sustained damage and nuke/dot/backup CC are gone.<br>
<br>
Druid: Circle of Seasons, Resist Cold, clicky regen, caster heals...  some nuking too, Ro's is particularly nice.  Most of those functions could be performed by another class, though.  I'm thinking their quick healing could use a boost.  I think Druids are much better off than Necros, raiding-wise.  Druids do pretty much the same thing on raids as they do in XP groups.<br>
<br>
Mage: M.O.D.R.O.D.  What else?  Maybe Mala if you don't have a Malo Shaman, nuke on gaters (if it's not M/F immune, which many seem to be).  Did I mention Modrod?  *Yawn*  Main grouping function of pet for sustained damage is gone.<br>
<br>
Enchanter:  Manaregen buffs, Tash, maybe Cripple... really you only need one or two per raid.  Many higher end mobs can't be CC'd so their main function from XP groups goes out the window...<br>
<br>
How bout other classes?  Melee's do damage and tank in XP groups, they continue to do this on raids.  Monks pull and do damage in XP groups, same on raids.  Clerics keep the MT/MA alive on raids, same as when XP'ing.  Shamans slow (when possible) and debuff, same as XP'ing, Wizards do massive quick damage in XP groups, on raids they can actually do very good sustained damage by using epic and eating mod rods, this is often preferable to Magi nuking because Wizards get lower resists (and have Banes and Lures for situations where it's impossible for a Mage to nuke).<br>
<br>
Everyone already knows that most Druid mains play ALTs on raids, or just don't g at all.  You rarely ever see Necros raiding any more, and most Magi only raid because their guild pressures them to make modrods.<br>
<br>
VI really needs to come up with something<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> fun</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for the above classes to do on raids, not just a &quot;give all your mana to someone more important than sit on your ass&quot; raid function. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zeem>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 287<br> <font color=#333333>(7/28/02 1:34:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=290.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Fun...</span><hr size=1> Acctually I have fun on raids. <br>
Ofcourse making modrods is a big part of our job, but in my opinion that is ok.<br>
On many encounters today AE aint the issue, it is crowdcontrol. And in many cases the crowdcontroll is simply to put a tank on a mob while others kill some other mob. <br>
More or less all encounters today is a matter of time too, so basicly every little dmg your pet can do count.<br>
So basicly on all these ring encounter I run around like a madman, making rods, make sure 5-12 tanks (depend on how many mages are on) always have a DS on, make sure pet is on the right mob, make sure pet is pulled out before enrage.<br>
<br>
I have very fun at these events, then ofcourse there are other events there my job simply to makemodrods before a big dragon (mostly because I stay ally cov). These event are less fun, but you can always play around with Eyes  :-).<br>
